  "local_port": 42658,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the salary of employee working in media?",
  "response": "Salaries for employees working in media can vary widely depending on factors such as job role, experience, location, and the size of the media company. Here are some general salary ranges for common positions in the media industry in the United States:\n\n1. **Journalist/Reporter:**\n   - **Entry-level:** $30,000 - $40,000 per year\n   - **Experienced:** $45,000 - $70,000 per year\n\n2. **Editor:**\n   - **Entry-level:** $35,000 - $50,000 per year\n   - **Experienced:** $55,000 - $85,000 per year\n\n3. **Producer (TV/Film/Radio):**\n   - **Entry-level:** $40,000 - $60,000 per year\n   - **Experienced:** $65,000 - $100,000+ per year\n\n4. **Digital Content Creator:**\n   - **Entry-level:** $30,000 - $45,000 per year\n   - **Experienced:** $50,000 - $80,000 per year\n\n5. **Media Sales Representative:**\n   - **Entry-level:** $35,000 - $50,000 per year (often with commission)\n   - **Experienced:** $55,000 - $90,000+ per year (including commission)\n\n6. **Public Relations Specialist:**\n   - **Entry-level:** $35,000 - $50,000 per year\n   - **Experienced:** $55,000 - $85,000 per year\n\nPlease note that these figures are approximate and can vary based on specific circumstances. It's always a good idea to research current salary trends and consult salary surveys specific to your region and industry for the most accurate information.",
